post_text:
ACE Leadership High school will be closed for three weeks beginning Monday, March 16, 2020, in response to the ongoing international coronavirus pandemic to all students and non-essential staff.
Students are scheduled to return to school on Monday, April 6, 2020.

The closure of all New Mexico public schools was ordered by Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham, the New Mexico Public Education Department, and the New Mexico Department of Health.

For the next three weeks, Lew Wallace Elementary will be open from 10 am to 1 pm for grab and go lunches starting March 16, 2020.

Events at ACE, including the Heavy Equipment Rodeo, Prom and our Spring Title 1 Family Meeting will be postponed until a later date.

Keep checking back for updates.

From all of us here at ACE stay safe and we will see you all soon.
text:
ACE Leadership High school will be closed for three weeks beginning Monday, March 16, 2020, in response to the ongoing international coronavirus pandemic to all students and non-essential staff.
Students are scheduled to return to school on Monday, April 6, 2020.

The closure of all New Mexico public schools was ordered by Gov. Michelle Lujan Grisham, the New Mexico Public Education Department, and the New Mexico Department of Health.

For the next three weeks, Lew Wallace Elementary will be open from 10 am to 1 pm for grab and go lunches starting March 16, 2020.

Events at ACE, including the Heavy Equipment Rodeo, Prom and our Spring Title 1 Family Meeting will be postponed until a later date.

Keep checking back for updates.

From all of us here at ACE stay safe and we will see you all soon.
